   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Forks can be bent out of shape by extreme overloading, glancing
blows against walls or other solid objects or using the fork tip as
a pry bar.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Bent or twisted forks are much more likely to break and cause
damage or injury. They should be removed from service
immediately.</p>
